It has been gathered that a Boko Haram commander, Modu Hajja Bunaye Bama, has been apprehended by the Civilian Joint Task Force in Bonro state. As disclosed in a Facebook post by Kolomi Shettima Kanuribe, the terrorist was nabbed during Boko Haram attack at Jiddari Polo, a suburb of Maiduguri, the Borno state capital last week. He has since been handed over to the appropriate authorities, according to reports. 